Description: Body sherd of grey ware pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe or amphora; dark grey to reddish fabric with limestone and some mica inclusions; worn dark grey slip on exterior. Drilled (through) for analysis.
Bibliographic references: Etruscan Bucchero / A Catalogue of Etruscan Bucchero in the British Museum (No. 235)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.156)
